<br>
This seems to be the model for this type of online game, I can't help think there must be a better way. I suppose dev's just can't think of any point to a game except making players goals more and more unattainable. I am very goal oriented and when levels really start to stretch out, I start to feel a bit guilty about hrs played. I have really been pushing to get to 100 and am close, (97) but it takes days to get a level now playing a few hrs a day. And FC hasn't made the experience any richer, particularly if you do missions, the layout are extremely repitive, mobs are all the same, just different level. I mean I have been impressed by the artwork in the game, but the programmers are creatively challenged IMO. One of the goals I had in other games was new experiences. Dev's made that possible as you advanced in level. New dungeon, new territories, new armor types, rare drops, quest items.........FC is all about cloning from low to high every experience. There is nothing unique to work toward. I played AC for a couple years, there were quest items, like bows, and other unique weapons, also unique armors and robes. Something to work for and look forward to. I am not aware of anything like that here. <br>
<br>
Where is is the interaction of dev's in game? In EQ dev's often took over high level mob's and had special events. They were fun. You get to know some of the people behind the game, it's a thrill, like the naming ceremony that EQ used to have. and you Hang out and just play and BS with the devs. Sometimes they left special items behind if you could defeat them........It just adds something cool to the game.......something out of the ordinary. .........FC just keeps turning out memo's from Philip Ross.........their idea of coolness and interaction I guess.<br>
<br>
Anyway.............I plan on trying to team alot more once I hit 100 and hopefully that will workout and be fun. I will keep going for awhile until I see MA additions FC promises. If they come within a couple months I will keep my acct, if not I just don't see any reason to continue.......... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/urypht.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rypht</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tiny Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#660000>(1/20/02 7:31:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1603.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://u2.lvcm.com/rypht/ryphtmini.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: game getting mind numbingly dull</span><hr size=1> I think you are right, I've put quite a bit of time into a number of professions, and it really does seem like a pointless circle.. I can see talking to a non-player going something like this<br>
